lzh_formatted:
  title: 寄佐郞趙瑚
  author: 柳淑
  language: lzh
  text: 七十人生自古稀。功名要路足危機。分陽終始亦萬幸。茅屋靑山無是非。
korean:
  title: 기좌랑조호
  author: 유숙
  language: kor
  text: |-
    칠십 인생은 옛부터 드물어라
    공명의 중요한 자리 위태로움 많느니
    분양의 완전한 한평생 만 번 다행이거니
    띠풀집 푸른 산에는 시비가 없도다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0940&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Letter to Vice-Magistrate Zhao Hu
  author: Yu Suk
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Life reaching seventy—rare since ancient days.
    The heights of glory hold a thousand perils.
    Yet to complete one's span in peace—what fortune!
    In a thatched cottage by green mountains, no right or wrong exists.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The reference to 'seventy' echoes Confucius's famous saying about reaching seventy and following one's heart without transgression, suggesting a reflection on the wisdom that comes with age.
  - key: ''
    value: The contrast between the dangerous pursuit of official position and the simplicity of rural life reflects a common theme in East Asian literati poetry—the tension between ambition and the freedom found in withdrawal from public life.
